55:00.731 --> 55:01.072
No, thanks.

55:02.714 --> 55:04.937
But Gene simply loves books, loves Tibetan books.

55:06.539 --> 55:21.338
And Gene is there also a bit modest here, as usual, because not only did he study with Dijin, who was probably the former scholar of his age, and was interested in every kind of textual tradition that one could find in Tibet.

55:21.622 --> 55:26.967
But he also studied with a number of the leading scholars of other traditions, other Tibetan Buddhist traditions as well.

55:28.348 --> 55:32.511
So in that sense, Dean is kind of on a very unusual background.

55:34.033 --> 55:43.201
And at what point do you start learning the language and really assimilating the culture, which everybody says that you know as much or more than anyone?

55:43.401 --> 55:43.781
No, no.

55:44.081 --> 55:50.447
It was largely because of the living with this family in Seattle when I was

55:50.933 --> 55:51.714
at the center.

55:52.575 --> 55:54.918
Like this guy who's here now, he's one of my oldest friends.

55:55.959 --> 55:56.100
Kiddo.

55:56.420 --> 55:57.021
Kiddo.

55:57.441 --> 56:03.329
He was the nephew of the guy who's become the Grand Abbot of all the Bumbos.

56:04.330 --> 56:05.612
